Name: pjson
Version: 0.2
Summary: Command-line tool to validate and pretty-print JSON and XML.
Home-page: http://igorgue.com/pjson
Author: Igor Guerrero
Author-email: igfgt1@gmail.com
License: MIT
Description: pjson
        =====
        
        Like `python -mjson.tool` but with moar colors (and less conf)
        
        ###Usage
        
            ⚡ echo '{"json":"obj"}' | pjson
            {
              "json": "obj"
            }
        
        ###Looks Like This
        
        Image for the haters:
        
        ![image](http://f.cl.ly/items/3R1M3b2j2o2v1z0z2U0E/Screen%20Shot%202012-07-19%20at%206.58.54%20PM.png)
        
        Small retina display images are fucking huge.
        
        ###Example With Curl
        
            ⚡ curl https://github.com/igorgue.json | pjson
        
        ###Install
        
        Install `pygments`:
        
            ⚡ pip install pjson
        
